docs.abstract: Critics say the company has not done enough to block false posts that have led to attacks in countries including Sri Lanka, Myanmar and India.

docs.abstract: An Ohio plant owner and his blue-collar workers alike voice support for President Trump’s tactics in the trade fight, even if it means sacrifice.
docs.snippet: An Ohio plant owner and his blue-collar workers alike voice support for President Trump’s tactics in the trade fight, even if it means sacrifice.
docs.lead_paragraph: COLUMBUS, Ohio — You might think that managers and workers at Banner Metals would be up in arms over the Trump administration’s trade policies. After all, tariffs on imported steel and aluminum have pushed raw-material prices up and margins down, forcing the company to delay plans to purchase a new $1 million cutting machine and hire two new employees to operate it.

headline.main: Tariffs Trim a Factory’s Profit, but Loyalty to Trump Endures
headline.print_headline: Tariffs Trim Ohio Plant’s Profits, But Support for Trump Is Steady

headline.print_headline: CBS Board to Meet on Moonves After Accusations

docs.abstract: The social media service said a new video hub called IGTV would allow users to post videos up to an hour in length.
docs.snippet: The social media service said a new video hub called IGTV would allow users to post videos up to an hour in length.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Expanding further beyond its origins as an app for sharing pretty photos, Instagram said on Wednesday that it will now allow users to post videos up to an hour long, a feature that will thrust it into direct competition with YouTube and its own parent company, Facebook.

headline.main: Instagram Allows Longer Videos in Challenge to YouTube
headline.print_headline: With Longer Videos, Instagram Challenges YouTube

docs.lead_paragraph: Q. I just got an email message from someone claiming to be a hacker who broke into my computer and used my webcam to watch me looking at adult websites. docs.abstract: The new tax law may determine whether it’s better to complete a divorce by Dec. 31 or wait until next year.
docs.snippet: The new tax law may determine whether it’s better to complete a divorce by Dec. 31 or wait until next year.
docs.lead_paragraph: Lawyers and accountants often push their clients to plan for unpleasant events. Better to be prepared now than to pay the consequences later. But the Republican tax law that took effect in January has added a new urgency for wealthy Americans contemplating divorce.

headline.main: Should You Get a Divorce Now or Later?
headline.print_headline: New Tax Laws Make Timing Divorce Tricky
